In previous papers, we explored a variety of GRMHD+ray tracing simulations for the accretion flow around Sgr~A$^*$ \citep{2015ApJ...799....1C}. These models were created using \texttt{HARM} \citep{2012MNRAS.426.3241N, 2013MNRAS.436.3856S} for the GRMHD simulations and \texttt{GRay} \citep{2013ApJ...777...13C} for solving the radiative transfer equation along null geodesics. We used simulations with a time resolution of $10\,GMc^{-3}$, where $G$ is the gravitational constant, $M = 4.3\times10^6\,M_\Sun$ is the mass of Sgr~A$^*$, and $c$ is the speed of light. For the remainder of this paper we employ gravitational units and set $G=c=1$. 

